<p>
<seg id=1> Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu appointed the top hardliner Sharon in government as minister of foreign affairs. </seg>
<seg id=2> The appointment was made right on the eve of the summit between Israel and Palestine in America on an interim peace agreement. </seg>
<seg id=3> According to the agreement Israel will hand more lands on the west bank of the Jordan River to Palestine. </seg>
<seg id=4> Sharon firmly insisted on setting up residential areas for Jews on the Westbank and opposed to compromise over the issue of withdrawal. </seg>
</p>
